<br>
Apparently he was one of those kids who gets teased a lot... and my guess is that his victims were kids who teased him.  It seems as though he had the targets selected and the event planned for quite some time, seeing as how he operated so smoothly and just dropped the gun without much of a fuss at all once he was done.<br>
<br>
There were rumors floating around the school as much as weeks beforehand, and one girl even went up to the principal and warned him, &quot;So-and-so is planning on bringing a gun to school and killing people.&quot;  And the principal did nothing.<br>
<br>
The senior, Aaron Rollins, is dead.  Incidentally, his father is in the volunteer fire department, and was one of the first ones on the scene.  As soon as he realized the victim was his son, he backed off and let the others administer the emergency medical procedures, but it was too late.  What a terrible twist of fate for the father.<br>
<br>
The freshman, Seth Bartell, is still in critical condition as far as I've heard.  He's really holding on, but he was shot once in the head and once in the chest.<br>
<br>
Please pray, and not just for Seth and Aaron, but for the shooter, too, because now he needs repentence.<br>
<br>
This was really close to home for me.  Rocori is in our conference for high school sports, and I've been there for speech meets and knowledge bowl competitions.  I didn't know the kids, but it could just have easily been my school, so I might as well have known them, and that really hit me.<br>
<br>
~Jaguwolf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vonalbro>VONALBRO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:navy;><b>Moderator and,<br>Lady of Good Cheer</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 370<br> <font color=#B87333>(9/27/03 10:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://groups.msn.com/_Secure/0QwCzBIwUv8W7zF37hMk5d2Fg1gGjCH4NVDV2aEEDmfZWPYYtpxbyWDu3oCGGn!h7Z8GOHVqiRpONsHzThX!4vt*eMHzBV8UCdLqqY!T1HFA/kittyav.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: these children, too...</span><hr size=1> They have my prayers {{{JAGUWOLF}}},<br>
